aa(lp102
VAt the moment,
p103
aVthere is no clear fair-trade solution.
p104
aVBut there has been a huge amount of progress.
p105
aVThe US has recently passed legislation
p106
aVto target bribery and misconduct in the Congo.
p107
aVRecent UK legislation could be used in the same way.
p108
aVIn February, Nokia unveiled its new policy on sourcing minerals in the Congo,
p109
aVand there is a petition to Apple to make a conflict-free iPhone.
p110
aVThere are campaigns spreading across university campuses
p111
aVto make their colleges conflict-free.
p112
aVBut we're not there yet.
p113
aVWe need to continue mounting pressure on phone companies
p114
aVto change their sourcing processes.
p115
aa(lp116
VWhen I first came to the UK, 21 years ago,
p117
aVI was homesick.
p118
aVI missed my family and the friends I left behind.
p119
aVCommunication was extremely difficult.
p120
aVSending and receiving letters took months \u2014
p121
aVif you were lucky.
p122
aVOften, they never arrived.
